lab_1.title: SSL connection check
lab_1.desc: URL with http found, please check if this URL need to be protected with SSL or not ,Keyword: NSURL with http / NSURL startswith(http://)

lab_2.title: Make use of security method
lab_2.desc: Cipher function found. Ensure no weak cipher function used in this application. Message digest function found. Ensure no weak message degist function used in this application. Signature function found. Ensure no weak signature function used in this application. MAC function found. Ensure no weak MAC function used in this application.

lab_3.title: Make use of security class
lab_3.desc: Cipher function found. Ensure no weak cipher function used in this application. Message digest function found. Ensure no weak message degist function used in this application. Signature function found. Ensure no weak signature function used in this application. MAC function found. Ensure no weak MAC function used in this application.

lab_6.title: Make use of SQLite deprecated functions
lab_6.desc:
sqlite3_aggregate_count',
	'sqlite3_expired',
	'sqlite3_global_recover',
	'sqlite3_memory_alarm',
	'sqlite3_soft_heap_limit',
	'sqlite3_thread_cleanup',
	'sqlite3_transfer_bindings' These functions are deprecated. In order to maintain backwards compatibility with older code, these functions continue to be supported. However, new applications should avoid the use of these functions. Keyword: libsqlite3.dylib

lab_8.title: Clipboard manipulation check
lab_8.desc: Any app on an iOS device can access the most recent thing copied to your clipboard.Theoretically, a malicious app can read what’s on your iOS clipboard and then feed that information back to a remote server. That remote server can be easily accessed by someone stealing your personal and sensitive information. Keyword: Foundation, copy: ,cut: ,paste:

lab_9.title: Make use of SMS related code
lab_9.desc: This application sends SMS message. One of the most common vulnerabilities of SMS verification codes is weak security protocols. Many SMS verification codes are sent over unencrypted channels, making them vulnerable to interception.Make sure it do this action with user permission. Keyword: MFMessageComposeViewController,canSendText

lab_10.title: Certificate check
lab_10.desc: Check the SSL Certificate information.We use SSLlab to check your cert,more information https://www.ssllabs.com/ssltest/ Keyword: NSURL startswith https://

lab_11.title: Base64 String decoding
lab_11.desc: Base64-encoded or base64-decoded string found Applications may Base64-encode parameters to conceal them from users or to ease the transfer of binary data. The existence of Base64-encoded data might suggest security-sensitive information or functionality that should be investigated further. Keyword: Base64

lab_12.title: Make use of javascript in webview
lab_12.desc: Webview JavaScript Enabled, the webview use setJavaScriptEnabled to allow javascript. It is potentially dangerous because it may allow the external website to do XSS attack in the webview. Keyword: UIWebView - stringByEvaluationgJavaScriptFromString in webview

lab_13.title: Screenshot detection
lab_13.desc: This application allows users to take screenshots.Please check screenshots function and turn it off. Keyword:UIApplication - _handleScreenshot to detect screenshot

lab_14.title: HTTPS ALLOW_ALL_HOSTNAME_VERIFIER check
lab_14.desc: This application use ALLOW_ALL_HOSTNAME_VERIFIER to verify all the CN. It is dangerous and may cause man-in-the-middle attack.

lab_18.title: WebView setAllowFileAccess
lab_18.desc: Allow local file access with webview. Please ensure your code not to allow path traversal.

lab_20.title: Possible hardcoded information
lab_20.desc: The use of a hard-coded password increases the possibility of password guessing tremendously. Keyword: CCCrypt, CCAlgorithm

lab_21.title: USE URL
lab_21.desc: URL found during analysis, check if there are some suspisious URL. Keyword:Use URL schemes with

lab_23.title: Local Data Storage
lab_23.desc: While it can improve the efficiency and availability of the application, it also carries risks. To protect the security of sensitive user information, a better approach is to store data in iOS's secure storage areas, such as the Secure Enclave.  Keyword:PrivateFrameworks

lab_24.title: Make use of log function
lab_24.desc: Log function in this application, you should notice is there sensitive information in these logs. Keyword: Foundation, NSLog

lab_25.title: Keyboard cache
lab_25.desc: Because the keyboard cache file is stored on the device, if the device is lost, it may be recovered, thereby revealing any sensitive information contained within. Check the keyboard cache ability open or not. Keyword: libSystem.B.dylib, Caches

lab_26.title: Domain Check
lab_26.desc: Connecting to an insecure domain may result in consequences such as virus/malware infection, data theft, identity theft, computer ransom, etc. It's important to only connect to secure domains and use up-to-date anti-virus software, firewall, and browser, and avoid entering sensitive information on insecure websites.

lab_27.title: use of PIE
lab_27.desc: Enabling Position Independent Executable (PIE) are mainly related to enhancing the security of applications.

lab_28.title: debug mode
lab_28.desc: Mobile applications should disable debug mode.
